title: SFH meets Singapore's Minister for Health (with photo)
content_text:
p>
	The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, today (December 3) met 
	with the visiting Minister for Health of Singapore, Mr Gan Kim Yong, to 
	exchange views on public medical and health issues and sign a Memorandum of 
	Understanding (MOU) to foster collaboration between the two places. At the meeting, Dr Ko briefed Mr Gan on Hong Kong's health-related policies 
	and the work of the Food and Health Bureau. Officials of the two governments

and the work of the Food and Health Bureau. Officials of the two governments 
	also exchanged views on issues relating to healthcare financing. The two parties also signed an MOU to enhance mutual co-operation on 
	health-related issues and the exchange of personnel for short-term 
	attachments, which will provide opportunities for the healthcare personnel 
	of both sides to learn from each other and strengthen communication. Dr Ko said, "Hong Kong has been maintaining exchanges with Singapore on the 
	medical and health fronts. Singapore's relevant policies and measures can

medical and health fronts. Singapore's relevant policies and measures can serve as a useful reference. I hope that both parties can continue to strengthen co-operation and experience sharing, which will be beneficial to Hong Kong in developing healthcare measures befitting the needs of the community." During his stay in Hong Kong, Mr Gan will call on officials of the Department of Health and the Hospital Authority as well as visit the Centre for Health Protection and a geriatric day hospital. Ends/Wednesday, December 3, 2014
